ynamo mechanism proposed in the 1990's produces an energy\nrelease that should have influence in the energy of the SN explosion. We extend\nthe work done previously done by \\cite{vink06} about the energetics of the SN\nexplosion looking for this energy release and we look for the element\nionization and the X-ray luminosity and we compare our results with other SNRs\nwith an associated central source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 6 Sep 2014 10:56:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Feb 2015 16:33:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-11"}
